===Logistics and operational improvements===
In December 2006, the South Korean military distributed a digital manual for the K10. The manual was developed with a budget of 1 billion KRW. It can easily identify the equipment composition, specifications, operation procedures, operating principles, maintenance tips, and signs of failure of the K10 ARV. It visualizes the vehicle in 3D virtual reality, so operators can easily understand compared to conventional text-based manuals.<ref>{{Cite web |script-title=ko:가상현실 이용한 'K-10' 교보재 개발 |url=https://n.news.naver.com/mnews/article/001/0001507135?sid=100 |access-date=2022-08-19 |website=[[Naver News]] |language=ko}}</ref> After seeing significant improvement in training efficiency, operating capability, and soldiers' maintenance skill, a digital manual was also adopted for the K9 in May 2007.<ref>{{Cite web |title=K-9 자주포 전자식 교보재 개발 완료 |url=https://n.news.naver.com/mnews/article/234/0000000096?sid=123 |access-date=2022-08-19 |website=[[Naver News]] |language=ko}}</ref>

In May 2018, an ABC (Automatic Bore Cleaner) model RB-155 by SDI (SooSung Defense Industries) was adapted for the South Korean K9. The automatic cleaner provides efficiency in maintenance by requiring just one person to clean the barrel in 20 minutes, with incomparable results compared to conventional cleaning.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mk.co.kr/news/society/view/2018/05/303633/ |script-title=ko:수성정밀기계, K9 자주포 자동청소기 국방부 공급 |publisher=[[Maeil Business Newspaper]] |date=2018-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |date=2014-11-12 |title=Automatic Bore Cleaner – Soosung Defense Industries, Ltd. |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v5OkA4FezoE  |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211222/v5OkA4FezoE |archive-date=2021-12-22 |url-status=live|publisher=SooSung Defense Industries LTD}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

As of June 2023, the localization rate is at 80%. Several minor upgrades were added, such as structural changes to the chassis to shorten the time to remove the power pack from hours to ten minutes.<ref>{{Cite web |last=이 |first=수기 |date=2023-06-20 |script-title=ko:폴란드·인도 사로잡은 K9 자주포..."다음 목표는 무인화" |url=https://www.joongang.co.kr/article/25170992 |access-date=2023-08-26 |website=[[JoongAng Ilbo]] |language=ko}}</ref>

On 8 December 2023, Norway, Finland, and South Korea signed an agreement for the two Nordic countries to share spare parts without submitting signed applications to South Korea. The agreement allows Norway and Finland to simply send a report after the parts sharing has occurred, which shortens processing time and thus improves logistics support.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Forsvarsdepartementet |date=2023-12-08 |title=Norway, Finland and South Korea have all signed an agreement to enhance Norwegian defence capabilities. |url=https://www.regjeringen.no/en/aktuelt/norway-finland-and-south-korea-have-all-signed-an-agreement-to-enhance-norwegian-defence-capabilities/id3017673/ |access-date=2023-12-18 |website=Regjeringen.no |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Mobility===
In October 2013, Daeshin Metal became the major parts supplier for Allison Transmission in making X1100-5A3 as an offset trade, further increasing localization. Applicated transmission will be equipped starting on the Batch X and the Batch V production of K9 and K10 respectively.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.korea.kr/news/pressReleaseView.do?newsId=155921390 |script-title=ko:절충교역 통해 중소기업 방산수출 530만불 달성 |publisher=Republic of Korea |date=2013-10-10}}</ref>

====Domestic engine====
[[File:STX SMV1000 engine.jpg|thumb|STX SMV1000 engine]]
In September 2020, the DAPA launched a project for indigenous engines for the vehicle. The project is expected to cost ₩75 billion over a period of 5 years.<ref>{{cite web|title='K9 자주포' 엔진 국산화 추진...내년부터 750억원 투입|url=https://news.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=5004470&ref=A|access-date=2021-08-31|website=[[KBS News]]|language=ko}}</ref>

On 31 May 2021, engine manufacturer [[STX Engine]] was selected as the winner after competing against Doosan Infracore (now [[HD Hyundai Infracore]]).<ref>{{cite news|last=황 |first=봉규|date=2021-05-31|title=STX엔진, K9 자주포 엔진 국산화 사업자 선정|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20210531114100052|access-date=2021-09-01|website=[[Yonhap News Agency]]|language=ko}}</ref>

On 26 November 2021, British engineering company [[Ricardo PLC]] has won a contract from STX Engine to help develop a clean-sheet engine for the K9 howitzer. Under the contract, STX Engine engineers will embed with Ricardo's engineering development team to facilitate knowledge transfer and accelerate development. Ricardo stated that the objective was to integrate seamlessly with the K9 vehicle to enable South Korean to resolve [[license]] barriers for [[export]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ricardo nets contract from STX Engine for South Korean project {{!}} Shephard |url=https://www.shephardmedia.com/news/landwarfareintl/ricardo-nets-contract-from-stx-engine-for-new-heav/ |access-date=2024-10-03 |website=www.shephardmedia.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2021-11-27|script-title=ko:[단독] 한화디펜스, K9자주포 국산 엔진 장착 추진|url=https://www.g-enews.com/view.php?ud=2021112708065213822bb03d9507_1|access-date=2021-12-12|website=[[Global Economic (newspaper)|Global Economic]]|language=ko}}</ref>

On 21 September at the DX Korea 2022 exposition, STX Engine presented a newly designed 1,000&nbsp;hp diesel engine for the K9.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-09-21 |title=[DX KOREA 2022] STX엔진, K9 자주포 1000마력 개발 엔진 등 소개 |url=https://www.fntimes.com/html/view.php?ud=20220921181932637999ebb03838_18 |access-date=2023-12-18 |website=FNTIMES |language=ko}}</ref>

On 8 December 2023, the media reported that STX Engine completed the [[durability]] test of the new engine, the SMV1000, and it will be installed on the howitzer for the driving test. The SMV1000 can be installed without requiring any structural changes to the K9, [[K10 ammunition resupply vehicle|K10]], or [[K21|AS21 Redback]], and is {{convert|76|kg|lb|sp=us}} lighter in weight, 5% better [[fuel efficiency]] compared to MT881, and has improved low-temperature startability. The SMV1000 will be installed in K9A1EGY and K10EGY for [[Egypt]] and AS21 for [[Australia]]. The new engine will replace the German design to avoid [[export restriction]]s.<ref name="KNnews 2024-09-27">{{cite web|url=https://www.knnews.co.kr/news/articleView.php?idxno=1443050|title=K9 자주포 국산 엔진 양산 성공… 창원서 1호 엔진 출고|publisher=[[Kyongnam Shinmun]]|date=27 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20241004232910/https://www.knnews.co.kr/news/articleView.php?idxno=1443050|archivedate=4 October 2024|accessdate=4 October 2024|author1=Jeon Gang-yong}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-08 |script-title=ko:[단독] STX엔진 'K9 자주포' 디젤엔진 국산화 내구도 시험 완료 "중동 추가수출 파란불" |url=http://www.bizhankook.com/bk/article/26737 |access-date=2023-12-21 |website=비즈한국 |language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-30 |title=ko:STX엔진, K9 자주포 엔진 국산화 '개가'..."수출 확대 청신호" |url=https://www.paxetv.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=213341 |access-date=2024-11-25 |website=PAX경제 |language=ko}}</ref> Egypt has purchased 355 engines at 134.8 billion KRW for its K9 program.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-28 |title='K9 자주포 엔진 부품 국산화' '장애인 운동보조 슈트형 로봇' 등 첨단 기술 총망라 |url=https://www.donga.com/news/Economy/article/all/20231227/122802578/1 |access-date=2023-12-30 |website=[[The Dong-A Ilbo]] |language=ko}}</ref><ref name="Egypt Engine">{{Cite web |date=2023-12-08 |script-title=ko:[단독] STX엔진 'K9 자주포' 디젤엔진 국산화 내구도 시험 완료 "중동 추가수출 파란불" |url=http://www.bizhankook.com/bk/article/26737 |access-date=2023-12-30 |website=비즈한국 |language=ko}}</ref>

On 4 February 2024, the first K9 with the SMV1000 engine was revealed at the World Defense Show 2024 in [[Saudi Arabia]], along with domestic [[automatic transmission]] from SNT Dynamics.<ref>{{Cite web |last=김 |first=동규 |date=2024-02-11 |title=獨 허가받고 수출하던 K-9 자주포, 국산엔진 달고 수출길 활짝 |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20240210025500003 |access-date=2024-02-19 |website=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=노 |first=주섭 |date=2024-02-05 |script-title=ko:방위사업 영토 넓히는 SNT… 최신 무기로 중동에 '눈도장' |url=https://www.fnnews.com/news/202402051914398094 |access-date=2024-02-19 |website=[[The Financial News]] |language=ko-KR}}</ref>

The STX Engine began [[mass production]] in September 2024 after completing the development of its domestic SMV1000 engine from 2020 to 2023 to circumvent [[export control]]s on German [[MTU Friedrichshafen|MTU]] engines in future [[International trade|export market]]s.<ref name="DAPA 2024-09-27">{{cite web|url=https://www.dapa.go.kr/common/nttFileDownload.do?fileKey=76739d7d59e357e599ad26066a10a09f|title=K9 자주포 국산 엔진 양산...K-방산 해외진출 이끈다|publisher=[[Defense Acquisition Program Administration]]|date=27 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240930170216/https://www.dapa.go.kr/common/nttFileDownload.do?fileKey=76739d7d59e357e599ad26066a10a09f|archivedate=30 September 2024|accessdate=30 September 2024|author1=}}</ref><ref name="iM SECURITIES STX Engine">{{cite web|url=https://file.alphasquare.co.kr/media/pdfs/company-report/[11073220]_077970.pdf|title=STX엔진|publisher=iM SECURITIES CO., LTD.|date=11 March 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20241002002552/https://file.alphasquare.co.kr/media/pdfs/company-report/%5B11073220%5D_077970.pdf|archivedate=2 October 2024|accessdate=2 October 2024|author1=}}</ref> With the development of domestic engines after three years of development, all 500 German-made parts previously used in German MTU engines have been replaced with parts developed in South Korea. The domestic engine will be proposed or supplied as an alternative to the German-made engine to countries that are banned from exporting German products when exporting the K9 in the future.<ref name="DAPA 2024-09-27" /><ref name="iM SECURITIES STX Engine" />

===Protection===
On 7 May 2021, Hanwha Defense announced a cooperation with the Australian company HIFraser in supplying AFSS for AS9 and AS10 for Australia. HIFraser will start to assist Korean company DNB Co in delivery of AFSS to Korean operated K9s as well.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-05-07|script-title=ko:한화디펜스, 호주 엔지니어링 회사와 계약..."차량화재 안전성 강화"|url=http://www.theguru.co.kr/news/article.html?no=21287|access-date=2021-09-01|website=www.theguru.co.kr|language=ko}}</ref>

In February 2022, Hanwha Defense signed a [[memorandum of understanding]] with the Australian company Bisalloy Steels in supplying armor plate for the AS9, AS10, and AS21 Redback to reduce manufacturing cost and to strengthen their partnership. Hanwha Defense plans to use armour steel from Bisalloy Steels for foreign exports, including an Egyptian variant, while [[POSCO]] continues to supply steel for domestic production.<ref>{{cite web|last=tf.co.kr|date=2022-02-15|script-title=ko:한화디펜스,이집트 수출·K-9자주포에 호주산 강재 쓴다|url=http://news.tf.co.kr/read/economy/1918807.htm|access-date=2022-02-20|website=더팩트|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2022-02-16|title=K9 자주포 수출 물량, 국산 방탄강 후판 아닌 호주산 철강 적용키로|url=http://www.snmnews.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=491107|access-date=2022-02-20|website=철강금속신문|language=ko}}</ref>

==Upgrades==

===K9A1===
In September 2010, a major issue regarding the engine was brought up by the defense committee. According to the report, a total of 38 K9s experienced engine cavitation since 2005. Initial investigation prior to the discussion suggested that the use of 3rd party manufactured antifreeze may have caused the engine cavitation.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010090820401777060 |title=K-9 자주포에 엉뚱한 부동액 넣어 엔진 고장 |publisher=Asian Economy |date=2010-09-08}}</ref> Using the recommended TK-6-03-01012 antifreeze did not solve the problem, suggesting that the antifreeze was not the cause of the issue.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.heraldcorp.com/military/view.php?ud=20100909000969 |title=K-9 자주포, 전용 부동액도 이상 |publisher=[[Herald Corporation]] |date=2010-09-09}}</ref> A member of the defense committee mentioned that the Turkish T-155, which uses an identical mobile system but has an APU (auxiliary power unit) installed, never reported such a case.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.naver?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=100&oid=001&aid=0004649623 |script-title=ko:안규백 "K-9 자주포, 전용부동액에도 이상" |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=2010-09-09}}</ref> The military chose to study the issue further by monitoring how antifreeze affects the engine, and testing the APU when the vehicle is in idle.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010091514395704230 |script-title=ko:[주력무기 K계열 무엇이 문제인가]②삼성테크윈의 K9자주포 |publisher=Asian Economy |date=2010-09-15}}</ref> Installing an APU on the K9 was discussed during its development phase, but was not adapted for mass production.<ref name="K9 Upgrade feature">{{cite AV media |date=2020-11-08 |script-title=ko:[군금해?!] 진화하는 K9자주포 |language=ko |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kRM7R2FOhBY |publisher=국방TV}}</ref>

In September 2011, the Defense Committee addressed issues regarding the K9 Thunder's FCS (fire control system), noting that its computer and OS (operating system) are discontinued and outdated, thus increasing related logistics cost by 70% over past 3 years. India expressed the same concern during evaluation. The first produced 24 K9s are equipped with [[i386]] and the rest are with [[i486]]; [[DOS]] is installed on both types. On the other hand, Samsung Techwin argued that both the processor and the OS are widely used in the military including newly produced weapons, that older CPUs are more durable, and that DOS has a lower failure rate.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ddaily.co.kr/news/article/?no=82546 |title=K-9 자주포에 왜 386컴퓨터와 DOS를 쓸까? |publisher=Digital Daily |date=2011-09-22}}</ref>

The military was determined to launch a FCS upgrade program starting in 2013 for both logistical reason's and Australia's request.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.naver?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=100&oid=001&aid=0005272402 |title="2011년 생산 K-9에 99년형 386급 도스컴퓨터" |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=2011-09-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.naver?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=100&oid=086&aid=0002072332 |script-title=ko:육군, 수도군단 해체계획 "없던 일로" |publisher=The Naeil News |date=2011-09-29}}</ref> In December 2013, the DAPA awarded Samsung Techwin as a main provider for the K9 upgrade program.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.etoday.co.kr/news/view/842783 |script-title=ko:삼성테크윈, 방위사업청과 6126억 규모 공급 계약 |publisher=eToday |date=2013-12-24}}</ref>

In March 2015, the South Korean military announced that Samsung Techwin was developing a driver's safety system, as a consequence of an accident resulting in the death of an operator in January 2015. Under the safety system, the turret rotation automatically stops if the driver's hatch remains open and is at a dangerous angle to the driver. The feature can be turned off if necessary.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.donga.com/news/article/all/20150303/69911577/1 |script-title=ko:'조종수 사망' K-9 자주포 성능개선키로 |publisher=[[The Dong-A Ilbo]] |date=2015-03-03}}</ref>

In August 2017, the DAPA approved the serial production of upgraded K9s. K9A1 upgrades include an automatic FCS, combining GPS system to INS, an improved driver's night periscope with thermal frontal camera, a rear view camera, and a driver's safety system. The 8&nbsp;kW [[auxiliary power unit]] (APU) is provided by Farymann & TZEN co, Ltd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tzen.co.kr/english/product/product3.html|title=Auxiliary Power Units(APU)|publisher=Farymann & TZEN|date=2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220307115325/http://www.tzen.co.kr/english/product/product3.html|archive-date=7 March 2022|access-date=7 March 2022|author=Farymann & TZEN}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=03762166622653904&mediaCodeNo=257&OutLnkChk=Y|script-title=ko:방산 중소기업 '페리만&티젠', 궤도차량 수평식 디젤엔진 선보여|publisher=[[Edaily]]|date=17 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220307120453/https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=03762166622653904&mediaCodeNo=257&OutLnkChk=Y|archive-date=7 March 2022|access-date=7 March 2022|author=Kim Gwanyong}}</ref> A1 standard also allows to shoot new extended range ammunition.<ref name="Hanwha Defense K9" /> All Korean K9s will receive A1 upgrades along with a 12-year cycle overhaul at the Army Consolidated Maintenance Depot starting in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=3535685&ref=A |title=軍, 육군·해병대 K-9 자주포 내년부터 성능개량 |publisher=[[Korean Broadcasting System]] |date=2017-08-18}}</ref><ref name="CMD 2022">{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qRHK6pj-u-E |title=[K9A1, 명품의 재탄생] K9 자주포 완전분해! 성능개량+창정비 현장! |date=2022-02-06 |last=KFN뉴스 |access-date=2024-09-18 |via=YouTube}}</ref> The first K9A1 joined the Republic of Korea Army in August 2018.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1S3HI4W3GE |script-title=ko:자동사격통제·보조동력 장착¨더 세진 '개량 자주포' 떴다 |publisher=Seoul Economics |date=2018-08-24}}</ref> According to the magazine published by the DAPA in October 2024, South Korea plans to upgrade 600 vehicles to A1 standard.<ref name="600 K9A1">{{Cite web |script-title=ko:청아람 :: 사업편 :: 정확도를 높이는 위력 장착을 위해 |url=https://dapa-magazine.kr/page/vol138/02.html |access-date=2024-11-29 |website=dapa-magazine.kr |language=ko}}</ref>

Details of the K9A1 upgrade:<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:[단독] 육군7포병여단 백호대대, K9A1 자주포 사격훈련|url=https://kookbang.dema.mil.kr/newsWeb/20210804/11/BBSMSTR_000000010023/view.do|access-date=2021-09-01|website=[[Kookbang Ilbo]]|archive-date=4 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404145639/https://kookbang.dema.mil.kr/newsWeb/20210804/11/BBSMSTR_000000010023/view.do|url-status=dead}}</ref>
* Installation of APU : The APU allows the vehicle to react and fire without running the main engine, thus reduces fuel consumption. Crew members can operate without being exposed to the engine noise. Since the engine no longer needs to operate when the vehicle is stationary, the cost for engine maintenance was reduced.
* Enhanced driver's system : The driver's night periscope was changed from [[image intensifier]] to [[FLIR]], and can be viewed from the monitor. A rear view camera was installed. The driver's safety system disables the turret to rotate at a certain angle when the driver's hatch is open. The feature can be turned off if necessary.
* GPS : By combining INS and GPS, the vehicle can locate itself more precisely and faster by complementing each other, which also increases accuracy.
* Enhanced FCS : The computer and OS are upgraded. Software such as a field manual and ammunition monitoring are installed. The FCS is fully automated by using an electronic fuse setter and ammunition management system. The new FCS occupies less space, and is programmed for new extended range ammunition (60&nbsp;km).

===K9A2===

In May 2016, the DAPA announced the concept for a robotic howitzer at the international artillery conference held in the United Kingdom. The DAPA then launched several projects consisting of [[insensitive munition|insensitive charge]], better rifling of the main gun, and a fully automated loading system. The upgraded K9 will have longer range, faster firing rates, and reduced crew members—similar capabilities to the United States' canceled [[XM2001 Crusader]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1KXSI4SCIA |script-title=ko:크루세이더급 K-9 탄생하나? |publisher=Seoul Economics |date=2016-06-30}}</ref>

In August 2021, the ADD and Hanwha Defense completed the development of a high-response artillery automation system started in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-20 |script-title=ko:한화디펜스, 방위산업수출 첨병...K9 자주포 5조 계약 |url=https://www.mk.co.kr/news/special-edition/view/2022/04/350104/ |access-date=2022-06-05 |website=[[Maeil Business Newspaper]] |language=ko}}</ref> The new system is essential for a future remote controlled variant, and will enable a fully automated loading system including charges and fuse set—increasing the fire rate by 1.5 times.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-11-30|script-title=ko:진화하는 'K9 자주포'...산악·설원·정글·사막 다 통한다|url=https://www.nocutnews.co.kr/news/5665581|access-date=2021-12-12|website=[[No Cut News]]}}</ref> Developers originally designed munitions to be stored in the chassis. Due to the limited turret rotation, gun elevation, and to reduce the distance of munitions moving to the chamber for faster reloading, the location of the munitions was changed from the chassis to the turret.<ref name="K9A2 UK interview"/>

The [[Republic of Korea Armed Forces]] will confirm the ROC for K9A2 Block-I upgrade in March 2022. The K9A2 is expected to be operational by 2027. The military is designing the K9A3, with a firing range of 100&nbsp;km.<ref>{{cite web|last=정 |first=동훈|date=2022-02-17|script-title=ko:[단독] K-9 '괴물' 자주포로 재탄생 '자동장전' 성능개량 다음달 확정|url=https://imnews.imbc.com/news/2022/politics/article/6342500_35666.html|access-date=2022-02-20|website=[[MBC News]]|language=ko}}</ref> The operational K9A2 technology demonstrator was revealed to the public by Hanwha Defense in February 2022.<ref name="K9 Egypt & K9A2">{{Citation|title=Global No. 1 SPH, K9 Thunder| date=21 February 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zISxRSaW-Lc|language=en|access-date=2022-02-22}}</ref> In March 2022, the high-response artillery automation system was shown to the public.<ref name="JoongAng K9A2" /> The vehicle's turret is extended in length for installation of an autoloader. Its centre location is better than previous variants. The prototype weighs 48.5 t (combat) with metal tracks, which can be decreased by more than 2 t by switching to composite rubber tracks. Reduced weight can contribute to the installation of additional armor or subsystems.<ref name="K9A2 UK interview"/>

In July 2022, the Defense Acquisition Program Promotion Committee approved a proposal of 2.36 trillion KRW for 2023 to 2034 in development, and an upgrade of the K9A2 Block-I.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.konas.net/article/article.asp?idx=59036|title=K9자주포 국내연구개발로 성능개량|publisher=KONAS|date=18 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220803060222/https://www.konas.net/article/article.asp?idx=59036|archive-date=3 August 2022|access-date=3 August 2022|author=Choe Gyeongseon}}</ref>

In June 2023, the DAPA authorized the development of K9A2 Block-I with a budget of 2.36 trillion KRW for 2023 to 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |title='K9 자주포' 타격 능력 향상...4년간 2조3600억 원 투입 |url=https://kookbang.dema.mil.kr/newsWeb/20230627/1/ATCE_CTGR_0010020000/view.do |access-date=2023-08-26 |website=[[Kookbang Ilbo]] |language=ko |archive-date=26 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230826060959/https://kookbang.dema.mil.kr/newsWeb/20230627/1/ATCE_CTGR_0010020000/view.do |url-status=dead }}</ref> South Korea plans to upgrade basic K9s to K9A2 standard, and achieve full operational capability by 2034.<ref>{{Cite web  |date=2023-06-26 |title=K-9 자주포 '송탄·장전 자동화' 본궤도... 발사 속도 1.5배+인원 40%↓ |url=https://www.news1.kr/articles/5088096 |access-date=2023-08-26 |website=[[News1 (South Korean company)|News1]] |language=ko}}</ref>

During [[Eurosatory]] 2024, Hanwha revealed newer model of the K9A2, which resembles AS9 Huntsman rather than previous prototype with extended turret.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-19 |title=Korea to export K9 howitzers worth $920 mil. to Romania - The Korea Times |url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/southkorea/20240619/korea-to-export-k9-howitzers-worth-920-mil-to-romania |access-date=2025-07-02 |website=www.koreatimes.co.kr |language=en}}</ref> 

Details of the K9A2 upgrade:<ref name="JoongAng K9A2" /><ref>{{Citation |title=K9A2 리얼웨폰205 ㅣ국방홍보원 | date=22 August 2023 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YiezEI0XiSE |access-date=2023-08-26 |language=en}}</ref>
* Enhanced main gun: New rifling and chrome plating will increase barrel life from 1,000 EFC to 1,500 EFC, longer range, and allow faster firing rate.
* High-response artillery automation system: Key feature of the A2 and future A3 upgrade. Reduces crew number from 5 to 3 (2 in emergency) by installing a fully automated autoloading system, which increases the maximum firing rate from 6 to 8 rds/min to 9 to 10 rds/min and sustain firing rate from 2 to 3 rds/min to 4 to 6 rds/min.
* Increased sustained fire: All 48 rounds are located in the turret, and are accessible with the autoloader.
* Turret driving system: Changes from an electrohydraulic to an electric driving system.
* Automatic fire suppress system (AFSS): Enhanced fire suppress system for crew protection.
* Remote controlled weapon station (RCWS): Enables use of a secondary weapon without exposing a crew member.
* Air conditioning: Increases crew comfort by cooling down the temperature.
* Modular charge system (MCS): Provides crew protection from secondary explosions due to enemy fire including heavy weapons, by adapting insensitive charge, and required for the automatic loading process.
* Composite rubber track (CRT): Provides crew comfort by reducing vibration, noise, and lesser required maintenance. Reduced weight improves the vehicle's operational range. The rubber has a lower fatality from fragments to surrounding soldiers, compared to metal when under attack.<ref name="K9 UK partners interview"/>
* Enhanced armor: Anti-tank mine protection. Similar to the AS9 Huntsman standard.{{char|?}}

===K9A3===

In 2020, the DAPA announced the K9A3 upgrade plan will apply unmanned technology and achieve 100&nbsp;km shooting distance using gliding ammunition. The DAPA talked about the development of a super long-range cannon or a [[railgun]] to be mounted on the next generation of self-propelled howitzers.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-24 |script-title=ko:미·러, 사거리 100km 미래형 자주포 경쟁에 K-9도 진화 중 |url=https://www.g-enews.com/article/Industry/2022/04/20220424132740533414fb262fcb_1 |access-date=2022-06-05 |website=[[Global Economic (newspaper)|Global Economic]] |language=ko}}</ref>

In September 2022, the ADD began research into increasing the firing range of the howitzer. The new variant is expected to equip a 58 caliber gun, similar to the [[US Army]]'s [[M1299 howitzer]] and ramjet munitions to achieve a maximum range greater than 80&nbsp;km. The project is scheduled to be 60 months long, completing in August 2027.<ref>{{Cite news |last=김 |first=지헌 |date=2022-11-13 |title=K-9 자주포, 80km 너머 포탄 날린다...초장사정 체계 개발 착수 |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20221111149100504 |access-date=2022-12-02 |website=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |language=ko}}</ref> In November 2022, the Defense Acquisition Program Promotion Committee approved 440 billion KRW between FY2024 and FY2036 to develop and acquire precision guided munitions for the K9 platform.<ref>{{Cite news|last=하 |first=채림|date=2022-11-28|script-title=ko:국산 소형무장헬기 양산...한국판 스파이크·엑스칼리버 개발(종합)|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20221128044851504|access-date=2022-12-04|website=[[Yonhap News Agency]]|language=ko}}</ref>

In October at the Korea Army International Defense Industry Exhibition (KADEX) 2024, Hanwha Aerospace showcased a small-scaled model of the K9A3, which no longer resembles external appearance of earlier variants. Each K9A3 is remotely controlled by an operator from the K11A1 FDCV, and every K11A1 carries three operators and one commanding officer. To enable this, the K9A3 is equipped with LiDAR (autonomous driving assistance) and a driving camera(s) on the front, driving assistance cameras on the sides, and a remote communication device on the top of the turret.<ref name="K11A1">{{Cite web |last=박 |first=수찬 |date=2024-10-06 |title="K9 자주포, 괴물로 변한다" 1등 넘어 '싹쓸이' 특명 [박수찬의 軍] |url=https://www.segye.com/newsView/20241005510650 |website=[[Segye Ilbo]]}}</ref>

==Variants==

===K10 ARV (ammunition resupply vehicle)===
{{Main|K10 ammunition resupply vehicle}}

The K10 ARV is an automatic resupply vehicle based on K9 platform, sharing most of the components and characteristics. Its concept study started in November 1998 by Samsung Aerospace Industries and [[Pusan National University]]. Its design began in February 2002 by Samsung Techwin (previously Samsung Aerospace Industries), the ADD, and the DTaQ (Defense Agency for Technology and Quality), The army declared its completion in October 2005. The first vehicle rolled out in November 2006, with a price tag of 2.68 billion KRW. It was assigned to the 1st Artillery Brigade of the [[Republic of Korea Army]]. South Korea became the first nation to operate such type of military equipment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=001&aid=0000131318 |title=KDX-III 전투체계 5월 선정 |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=2001-02-14}}</ref><ref name="K10 ARV">{{cite news |url=https://www.asiae.co.kr/article/2009090418065348850 |title=K9자주포만 따라 다니는 차량 |publisher=[[The Asia Business Daily]] |date=2011-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hankyung.com/politics/article/2005100415588 |script-title=ko:로봇형 탄약운반장갑차 K10 개발 |publisher=[[The Korea Economic Daily]] |date=2005-10-04 |archive-date=5 April 2023 |access-date=17 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405151635/https://www.hankyung.com/politics/article/2005100415588 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.naver?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=100&oid=003&aid=0000616022 |script-title=ko:'서울 에어쇼' 국내 항공방위산업 새 지평 열었다 |publisher=[[Newsis]] |date=2007-10-24}}</ref>

The vehicle has a combat weight of 47 metric tons,<ref name="Hanwha Defense K10 ARV">{{cite web |url=https://www.hanwha-defense.co.kr/kor/products/firearms-system-k10.do |title=Hanwha Defense K10 ARV |access-date=17 July 2021 |archive-date=17 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210717233724/https://www.hanwha-defense.co.kr/kor/products/firearms-system-k10.do |url-status=dead }}</ref> and can support a K9 team by carrying and resupplying 104 shells of 155&nbsp;mm artillery ammunition and 504 units of charges under heavy fire. The vehicle is operated by a 3-person crew, requiring only one loader by applying fully automated control system. It transfers ammunition at a maximum speed of 12 rounds/min. It takes 37 minutes to fully load, and 28 minutes to empty the K10.<ref name="K10 ARV" /> It is often called the ''briquette car'' by military and defense industry officials.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2006-08-29 |script-title=ko:[커버스토리]방위산업 '손 큰 로비'가 주도한다 |url=http://weekly.khan.co.kr/khnm.html?mode=view&dept=113&art_id=12682 |access-date=2022-08-19 |website=[[Weekly Kyunghyang]] |language=ko}}</ref>

===K10 AARV (armored ammunition resupply vehicle)===
The K10 AARV is an enhanced protection variant of the K10 ARV. The first of its kind will be produced in Australia as the '''AS10'''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hanwha-defense.co.kr/eng/media/news-view.do?idx=1463&searchOption=&searchInput=&search=true&page=2 |title=Hanwha Defense shortlisted for Australian SPH project |publisher=Hanwha Defense |date=2020-09-03 |access-date=13 July 2021 |archive-date=13 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210713080014/https://www.hanwha-defense.co.kr/eng/media/news-view.do?idx=1463&searchOption=&searchInput=&search=true&page=2 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===K11 FDCV (fire direction control vehicle)===
The K11 FDCV is designed for the Egyptian military to provide [[command and control]], reconnaissance, and communication for armored vehicles. The vehicle is based on K10, and has a high mobility.<ref>{{cite web|date=2022-02-03|script-title=ko:한화디펜스, 이집트와 2조원 규모 K9 수출 계약|url=https://www.ebn.co.kr/news/view/1518292|access-date=2022-02-20|website=EBN|language=ko}}</ref>

===K11A1 FDCV===
First appeared publicly at the KADEX 2024, the K11A1 FDCV is designed to operate up to three K9A3 howitzers remotely. Each K11A1 carries three operators and a commander, and two K11A1s are teamed up to control a total of six K9A3s to form a battery. The vehicle is armed with the K6 HMG-mounted RCWS with the capability to shoot down drones using AI technology, anti-air missile launchers, and additional armor plate for mine protection.<ref name="K11A1"/><ref>{{Cite web |last=Triffaux |title=Hanwha Aerospace Designs Next-Gen K11A1 Fire Direction Control Vehicle for Remote Operation of K9A3 Sel-Propelled Howitzers |url=https://www.armyrecognition.com/news/army-news/army-news-2024/hanwha-aerospace-designs-next-gen-k11a1-fire-direction-control-vehicle-for-remote-operation-of-k9a3-sel-propelled-howitzers |access-date=2024-11-05 |website=www.armyrecognition.com |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-02 |script-title=ko:[단독] 한화, 차세대 자주포 K9A3 모형 최초 공개 |url=https://www.bizhankook.com/bk/article/28338 |access-date=2024-11-26 |website=비즈한국 |language=ko}}</ref>

==Operational history==

===2000s===
In October 2003, the K9 Thunder was evaluated by [[Spain]] at the military base located in [[Zaragoza]].<ref name="Defense Today K9">{{cite web |url=http://www.defensetoday.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=885 |title=K9 자주포 & 해외수출 Q&A |date=7 May 2020 |publisher=Defense Today}}</ref>

In 2004, the K9 was sent to [[Malaysia]] to test its operational capability in a tropical rainforest environment.<ref name="Defense Today K9" />

===2010s===
[[File:2010.11.25 해병대 연평도 k-9사격 (7445570778).jpg|thumb|right|A North Korean artillery attack near-misses a K9 Thunder, igniting fire on charges placed outside of the vehicle in November 2010.]]

{{See also|2010 Yeonpyeong bombardment}}

The K9 Thunder saw its first artillery vs artillery combat during the [[bombardment of Yeonpyeong]] in November 2010. After receiving a surprise artillery attack from North Korea, the 7th Artillery Battery of the [[Republic of Korea Marine Corps]] were tasked for a counterattack with the K9 howitzers stationed on the island. Prior to the attack, four howitzers had been on a scheduled firing exercise, and two remained in their fortified bunkers. During firing exercise, one vehicle had experienced a shell stuck in the barrel due to a misfire from a faulty charge. After the exercise, crews had opened the hatches of the vehicles and some had dismounted while waiting for the disabled gun to be fixed.<ref name="Battle of Yeonpyeong">{{cite web |url=https://www.haebyeong.com/free/48252 |title=ROKMC memoir |publisher=Republic of Korea Marine Corps |date=2010-12-14}}</ref>

Howitzers on the island always store 20 shells of HE and flares combined, excluding training rounds, for a rapid response.<ref name="20 rounds">{{cite news |url=https://www.korea.kr/news/actuallyView.do?newsId=148702508 |script-title=ko:연평도 K-9 자주포 B/L탄 20발 항상 적재 |publisher=Republic of Korea |date=2010-11-28}}</ref> The marines on the island had been operating the [[AN/TPQ-36 Firefinder radar|AN/TPQ-36]] and [[AN/TPQ-37 Firefinder radar|AN/TPQ-37]] radar, but the number of radar units was not sufficient to cover the long fortified North Korean coastline that the marines were facing.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010081011485232351 |title=北 해안포 NLL이남지역에 탄착(종합) |publisher=Asian Economics |date=2010-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.newdaily.co.kr/site/data/html/2010/08/15/2010081500017.html |script-title=ko:"남북, 서해5도서 대결땐 남한이 패한다" |publisher=[[Newdaily]] |date=2010-08-15}}</ref>

The first wave of North Korean bombardment damaged three out of four guns participating in the exercise. Some howitzers received internal damage from shrapnel entering through opened hatches, and one vehicle had an external fire. However, none of the crews suffered casualties, with the exception of a sergeant who had a cut injury from shrapnel.<ref name="Battle of Yeonpyeong" />
* Gun 1: communication system damage and external fire
* Gun 2: severe external damage
* Gun 3: communication system, autoloading system damage, and a crew injury
* Gun 4: barrel disabled from the exercise

After relocating to fortified positions, three howitzers (guns 2, 5, 6) fired back at the North Korean military structures located in Mudo because the marines were unable to track and locate the source of the attack. At the same time, marines worked on restoring communication with guns 1 and 3 by installing wires. Gun 1 went through extensive fire extinguishing while gun 3 joined the firing mission by switching automatic loading to manual loading.<ref name="Battle of Yeonpyeong" /><ref>{{Cite web  |date=2024-02-22 |title=Military Knew of N.Korean Artillery Move Before Attack |url=https://www.chosun.com/english/national-en/2010/11/26/VTJJGOYXRJFHIXQH72HILRXPUE/ |access-date=2024-11-28 |website=[[The Chosun Ilbo|The Chosun Daily]] |language=ko}}</ref>

Four howitzers were able to employ counter-battery fire during the second wave of the North Korean attack. The radar detected the KPA artillery positions in Kaemori, and two militaries exchanged artillery fire. The KPA attack caused a blackout of the ROK base, but the marines responded with an emergency generator. Additional and different types of ammunition were supplied by hand-carrying at the gun emplacements.<ref name="Battle of Yeonpyeong" /><ref name="20 rounds" />

In May 2011, K9 performed direct shooting for the first time.<ref>{{cite AV media |date=2011-06-10 |script-title=ko:국내 최초로 시도된 K-9자주포 직접조준사격 동영상! |language=ko |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k9JdYVxEReM  |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211222/k9JdYVxEReM |archive-date=2021-12-22 |url-status=live|publisher=국방TV}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ajunews.com/common/redirect.jsp?newsId=20110518000491 |script-title=ko:기계화부대 막강화력 총출동...위용 과시 |publisher=[[Aju Business Daily]] |date=2011-05-18}}</ref> K9 can strike bullseye from a distance of 1&nbsp;km with direct fire.<ref name="JoongAng K9A2" /> Per ROK military guidelines, the K9 fires ammunition with the maximum propellants (stage 6) to achieve a muzzle velocity of 1,0XX&nbsp;m/s, which changes based on the temperature of the gun, to maintain a straight line of ballistics for the targets at 400 meters while setting the limit of the maximum effective range at 1,500 meters (without the gunner's optics).<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qd7KzmtYNe8 |title=K9 포구 초속측정...직접조준 사격으로 대대급 화력 보여줘 |date=2022-07-27 |last=KFN뉴스 |access-date=2024-12-06 |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kxtidOUh2Ag |title=K9A1이 직접 조준사격(직사)를 하는 이유 대공개 ☆ 본격 밀리터리 Q&A! I 국방홍보원 |date=2024-07-24 |last=KFN |access-date=2024-12-06 |via=YouTube}}</ref>

[[File:A live fire exercise of the ROK Marine Corps K9 battery.webm|thumb|The [[live fire exercise]] of the ROK Marine Corps to prepare for the [[M-1978 Koksan|North Korean long-range artillery]] attack]]

In August 2016, the K9 was tested by the military of the United Arab Emirates. The vehicle managed to drive in the desert at maximum speed for one hour nonstop, without any malfunctions.<ref name="salesperson interview" />

In August 2017, a K9 operated by the 5th Artillery Brigade of the Republic of Korea Army was set ablaze during a firing exercise, causing 3 deaths and 4 wounds among crew members and instructors. After the investigation, it was found that a faulty spring caused the hammer to detonate prematurely, pushing the explosion into the vehicle before the breech was fully closed, and ignited the additional charges which had been taken out from the rack for the next firing. The entire K9 fleet operated by South Korea underwent inspection during the investigation. The Republic of Korea Armed Forces responded by installing black boxes and an AFSS (automatic fire suppression system), reinforcing maintenance, and providing flame-resistance uniforms to crew members.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.news1.kr/articles/?3190314 |title='K-9사고' 6대 후속조치 발표...난연전투복 보급(종합) |publisher=News1 Korea |date=2017-12-26}}</ref>

The production and the delivery of the K9 Thunder ended in June 2018. The factory will continue to produce the model as the K9A1 variant. The first new variant was fielded by the 5th Artillery Brigade of the Republic of Korea Army in August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-03-18|script-title=ko:한화디펜스 실적 이끈 K9 자주포...하반기 수출 총력전|url=https://biz.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/08/13/2019081302041.html|access-date=2021-08-31|website=[[ChosunBiz]]|language=ko}}</ref>

===2020s===
On 13 November 2020, the DAPA announced that the entire K9 program delivered to the Republic of Korea Armed Forces is now at full operational capability, bringing the K9 Thunder program for the South Korean military to completion.<ref>{{cite web|date=2020-11-13|script-title=ko:군, K9 자주포 실전 배치 20년만에 마무리...전력화 종결|url=http://www.mbn.co.kr/news/society/4339774|access-date=2021-08-31|website=[[Maeil Broadcasting Network]]|language=ko}}</ref>

[[File:Indian K9 SPH at Ladakh during Indo-China Clashes .jpg|thumb|right|[[Indian Army]] K9 Vajra-T deployed on Ladakh plateau during [[2020–2021 China–India skirmishes|China–India skirmishes]]]]
In February 2021, the K9 Vajra-T was deployed to the Ladakh region during territorial tensions between China and India.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.armyrecognition.com/defense_news_may_2021_global_security_army_industry/india_has_deployed_k9_vajra_155mm_self-propelled_howitzers_in_ladakh_region.html |title=India has deployed K9 Vajra 155mm self-propelled howitzers in Ladakh region |date=29 May 2021 |publisher=Armyrecognition.com |access-date=2022-03-16}}</ref>

In December 2024, the Norwegian military experienced a shortage of the K9 VIDAR spare parts due to the discrepancy between expected versus actual consumption of parts. To prioritize maintaining the howitzers in operational status, the military responded by temporarily removing the K10s, which share many components with the howitzer, from active service for cannibalization. The K10s will return to active service once the military receives the next shipment from South Korea in February 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Pettersen |first1=Stephan |last2=Sørbø |first2=Krister |date=2024-12-03 |title=Norges nye artillerisystem er delvis ute av drift |url=https://www.forsvaretsforum.no/artilleri-artilleribataljonen-beredskap/norges-nye-artillerisystem-er-delvis-ute-av-drift/408549 |access-date=2024-12-17 |website=www.forsvaretsforum.no |language=nb-NO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-17 |title=Hanwha Aerospace delivers additional K9 howitzers and K10 resupply vehicles to Norway |url=https://defence-industry.eu/hanwha-aerospace-delivers-additional-k9-howitzers-and-k10-resupply-vehicles-to-norway/ |access-date=2024-12-17 |language=en}}</ref>

On 28 January 2025, the [[Syrian Democratic Forces]] released a video of FPV drone attacks on two Turkish T-155s located in Manbij. The first attack set a howitzer on fire, but the video itself proves that the fire was put out, and the gun appears to be fine during the second drone attack, which the video does not show results.<ref>{{Cite web |date=Jan 28, 2025 |title=SDF Press: 2 T-155 Firtina artillery destroyed by SDF kamikaze drones, southwest of Manbij, in response of Turkish terrorist attacks targeting civilians |url=https://x.com/RojavaNetwork/status/1884316260844069325 |website=X |publisher=Rojava Network}}</ref>

