On 25 March 2012, South Korean president [[Lee Myung-bak]] and the Indian [[Prime Minister of India|Prime Minister]], [[Manmohan Singh]] signed [[Memorandum of Understanding]] (MoU) to strengthen the economy and military exchanges.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.naver?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=123&oid=154&aid=0000003053 |script-title=ko:한·인도 공동성명 |publisher=[[Blue House]] |date=2012-03-25}}</ref> On 29 March 2012 at DEFEXPO, [[SAMSUNG TECHWIN|Samsung Techwin]] and [[Larsen & Toubro]] announced their partnership to produce the K9 Thunder in [[India]]. As per the agreement, Samsung Techwin will transfer key technologies, and the vehicle will be manufactured under license in India using 50 per cent of the domestic content such as FCS and communication system.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/indl-goods/svs/engineering/lt-samsung-join-hands-for-indias-howitzer-artillery/articleshow/12457051.cms?from=mdr |title=L&T, Samsung join hands for India's Howitzer artillery |publisher=The Economic Times |date=2012-03-29}}</ref>

Two units of K9 were sent to [[Thar Desert]], [[Rajasthan]] for firing and mobility test, and competed against Russian [[2S19 Msta|2S19]]. Operated by [[Indian Armed Forces|Indian military]] personnel, the K9 fired 587 Indian ammunitions including Nub round and drove a total distance of 1,000&nbsp;km. Maintenance test was conducted at [[Pune]], EMI (electromagnetic interference) test at [[Chennai]], and technical environment test was held in [[Bengaluru]] until March 2014. K9 Thunder achieved all ROC set by Indian military while the Russian counterpart failed to do so.<ref name="salesperson interview" /><ref name="Defense Today K9" /> Hanwha Techwin (previously Samsung Techwin) later told in an interview that the Russian engine performance dropped when the air density is low and in high temperature, the placement of the engine also resulted in the center of the mass located at the rear, making the vehicle difficult to climb high angles. On the other hand, K9 benefitted from automatic control system of the engine, providing the optimum performance based on given condition automatically—this was one of the decisive reason why India selected K9 over 2S19.<ref name="Defense Today K9 India">{{cite web |url=http://www.defensetoday.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=1694 |title=K9 자주포 인도수출 Q&A|date=28 August 2020}}</ref>

In September 2015, the Indian [[Ministry of Defence (India)|Ministry of Defense]] (MoD) selected Hanwha Techwin and Larsen & Toubro as preferred bidder to supply 100 '''K9 Vajra-T''' to the [[Indian Army]] after K9 outperformed 2S19 Msta-S and passed two-year trial.<ref>{{cite web|title = India's Newest Gun: Fast and Deadly|url = https://thediplomat.com/2015/10/indias-newest-gun-fast-and-deadly/|website = The Diplomat|access-date = 2015-10-09|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151011181059/https://thediplomat.com/2015/10/indias-newest-gun-fast-and-deadly/|archive-date = 2015-10-11|url-status = live}}</ref> On 6 July 2016, India agreed in purchasing 100 K9 Vajra-T for $750 million.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.konas.net/article/article.asp?idx=46180 |script-title=ko:한국산 K-9 자주포 100문 인도 수출.. 가격협상 마쳐 |publisher=Konas Net |date=2016-07-06}}</ref> On 29 March 2017, the [[Government of India]] approved budget of $646 million for purchasing 100 K9 Vajra-T.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20170402047700014?input=1195m |script-title=ko:국산 K-9 자주포 인도 수출...양국 국방협력 강화 |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=2017-04-02}}</ref> A formal contract of $310 million was signed between Hanwha Techwin and Larsen & Toubro in [[New Delhi]] on 21 April. Hanwha Techwin will supply first 10 K9 Vajra-T, and 90 will be license produced in India by Larsen & Toubro.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://newsis.com/view/?id=NISX20170421_0014846773&cID=10301&pID=10300 |title=K-9 자주포 100문 인도 수출 확정...3500억 규모 |publisher=[[Newsis]] |date=2017-04-21}}</ref>

K9 Vajra-T consist 14 major Indian manufactured systems, 50% of component by value, which include Nub ammunition capable [[Fire-control system|FCS]] and its storage, communication system, and environment control and NBC protection system. Additional systems were installed such as GPS (Gunner's Primary Sight) for direct firing capability, and South African APU, which was proven for desert operation—Korean APU was under development phase during Indian trial. The vehicle's overall design was modified to suitable for operation in desert and high temperature condition, including the change of firing rate to 3 rounds in 30 seconds.<ref name="Defense Today K9" /><ref name="Defense Today K9 India" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Global|first=IndraStra|title=Indian Army Inducts Two New Artillery Systems|url=https://www.indrastra.com/2018/11/Indian-Army-s-New-Artillery-Systems-004-11-2018-0021.html|journal=IndraStra|issn=2381-3652|access-date=2018-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118164856/https://www.indrastra.com/2018/11/Indian-Army-s-New-Artillery-Systems-004-11-2018-0021.html|archive-date=2018-11-18|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://kookbang.dema.mil.kr/newsWeb/20170424/72/BBSMSTR_000000010026/view.do |title=K9 '바지라' 인도 수출 |publisher=Republic of Korea Defense Media Agency |date=2017-04-23 |access-date=30 August 2021 |archive-date=28 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128225640/https://kookbang.dema.mil.kr/newsWeb/20170424/72/BBSMSTR_000000010026/view.do |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/defence/indian-army-gets-more-firepower-rajnath-singh-flags-off-51st-k9-vajra-t-gun/1825430/|title=Indian army gets more firepower! Rajnath Singh flags off 51st K9 Vajra-T Gun|date=2020-01-16|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>

In February 2020, media reported that [[IIT Madras]] along with [[IIT Kanpur]], [[Armament Research and Development Establishment]] (ARDE) and [[Research Centre Imarat]] (RCI) are working on redesigning an existing 155&nbsp;mm shell using [[ramjet]] propulsion that can cover 60&nbsp;km+ range. It will be compatible with K9 Vajra-T. The shell will use precision guidance kit for trajectory correction. IIT Madras is ensuring that [[Munitions India]] can manufacture the shells.<ref>{{cite news |last1=MP |first1=Sidharth |date=21 February 2020 |title=IIT-M working on next-gen Ramjet-powered 155mm artillery shells for Indian Army |publisher=WION |url=https://www.wionews.com/india-news/iit-m-working-on-next-gen-ramjet-powered-155mm-artillery-shells-for-indian-army-282090 |access-date=22 August 2022}}</ref>

The 100th vehicle was delivered to the Indian Army on 18 February 2021, completing the contract ahead the schedule.<ref>{{cite web|date=2021-02-20|script-title=ko:100번째 K9 바지라 자주포 인도육군에 인도...추가 발주 가능성도|url=https://www.g-enews.com/view.php?ud=202102201050227006c5557f8da8_1|access-date=2021-09-01|website=[[Global Economic (newspaper)|Global Economic]]|language=ko}}</ref> The tanks are being produced in L&T's facility in Armoured Systems Complex, [[Hazira]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-11-09 |title=Fortune India Exclusive: L&T eyes big growth in defence and aerospace |url=https://www.fortuneindia.com/enterprise/fortune-exclusive-lt-eyes-big-growth-in-defence-and-aerospace/119127 |access-date=2024-11-14 |website=Fortune India |language=en}}</ref>

In May 2021, it was reported that India's [[Defence Research and Development Organisation]] is working with Larsen & Toubro on a [[light tank]] using the K9 chassis with [[105 mm calibre|105&nbsp;mm]] or 120&nbsp;mm gun system to counter China's [[Type 15 tank]]. The light tank variant was opted out as the estimated vehicle weight exceeded 30[[Tonne|&nbsp;tonne]], limiting the places to operate.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Philip|first=Snehesh Alex|date=14 June 2021|title=India sets eyes on Russian Sprut light tanks to counter China, gets rare access to trials|work=The Print|url=https://theprint.in/defence/india-sets-eyes-on-russian-sprut-light-tanks-to-counter-china-gets-rare-access-to-trials/676057/|access-date=10 August 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=2021-05-16|script-title=ko:중국군에 맞설 인도 경전차 사업...국산 K21-105가 도전장|url=https://www.chosun.com/politics/politics_general/2021/05/16/KCSFGQ2YURB23H2MDLNAUN6XYI/|access-date=2021-09-01|website=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=ko}}</ref>

The Indian Army planned ordering an additional 40 K-9 Vajra-T from Larsen & Toubro as of 2021 after completion of high altitude trials at [[Ladakh]] under cold climatic conditions.<ref>{{cite web|last=Philip|first=Snehesh Alex|date=2021-08-09|title=Trials in Ladakh a success, Army looks at ordering 40 more K9 Vajra-T howitzers for mountains|url=https://theprint.in/defence/trials-in-ladakh-a-success-army-looks-at-ordering-40-more-k9-vajra-howitzers-for-mountains/711436/|access-date=2021-08-10|website=ThePrint|language=en-US}}</ref> India is also looking to export the K9 Vajra-T variant to third countries in collaboration with South Korea and industry partners.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Song|first1=Sang-ho|last2=Kang|first2=Yoon-seung|date=2021-10-21|title=Partnering with S. Korea, India seeks to export K9 howitzers to third countries: Indian secretary|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20211021006500325|access-date=2021-10-21|website=[[Yonhap News Agency]]|language=en}}</ref>

As per a report in 2022, the MoD could place a repeat order of 200 K9 Vajra-T worth {{INRConvert|9600|c|lk=on|year=2022}} after satisfactory performance of the guns at high altitude terrain.<ref>{{cite web|last=Unnithan|first=Sandeep|date=23 January 2022|title=What's behind a massive order for Made-in-India howitzers|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india-today-insight/story/what-s-behind-a-massive-order-for-made-in-india-howitzers-1903375-2022-01-23|access-date=2022-01-23|website=India Today|language=en}}</ref> The Batch II is to be equipped with enhanced engine suited for high altitude operation, and is expected to complete delivery by 2028.<ref>{{cite web|date=2022-01-24|script-title=ko:인도, 한화디펜스의 K9 바지라 자주포 200문 추가 주문|url=https://www.g-enews.com/article/Global-Biz/2022/01/2022012411093525382bb03d9507_1|access-date=2022-02-20|website=[[Global Economic (newspaper)|Global Economic]]|language=ko}}</ref>

The Acceptance  of Necessity (AoN) for first 100 units was cleared by 27 September 2022 by the Defence Acquisition Council (DAC). This will be followed by issuing [[request for proposal]] (RFP) to [[Larsen & Toubro|L&T]] and cost negotiations.<ref name="India Batch 2">{{Cite news |last=Philip |first=Snehesh Alex |date=27 September 2022 |title=China threat in mind, Army to order another 100 K9 Vajra howitzers from L&T, more to follow |work=ThePrint |url=https://theprint.in/defence/china-threat-in-mind-army-to-order-another-100-k9-vajra-howitzers-from-lt-more-to-follow/1144787/ |access-date=27 September 2022}}</ref> As of February 2023, Hanwha was under a discussion for an order of 100 additional units.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Indian Army orders 100 additional K9 howitzers |url=https://www.janes.com/defence-news/news-detail/indian-army-orders-100-additional-k9-howitzers |access-date=2023-05-20 |website=Janes.com |date=20 February 2023 |language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230403203952/https://www.janes.com/defence-news/news-detail/indian-army-orders-100-additional-k9-howitzers|archivedate=2023-04-03}}</ref> According to a report in May 2024, the clearance for next 100 units would be approved after the formation of a new government after [[2024 Indian general election]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dubey |first=Ajit |date=2024-05-29 |title=Major Make in India defence deals including K-9 Vajra, fighter jet engines on Centre's agenda |url=https://aninews.in/news/national/general-news/major-make-in-india-defence-deals-including-k-9-vajra-fighter-jet-engines-on-centres-agenda20240529164930/ |website=ANI News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Triffaux |title=Indian Army to Receive Additional 100 South Korean K9 Vajra Self-Propelled Howitzers |url=https://armyrecognition.com/news/army-news/army-news-2024/indian-army-to-receive-additional-100-south-korean-k9-vajra-self-propelled-howitzers |access-date=2024-08-02 |website=armyrecognition.com |language=en-gb}}</ref> The [[Cabinet Committee on Security]] cleared the purchase of 100 units on 12 December 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |title=CCS clears Rs 20,000 crore Make in India projects for Su-30 fighter jets, 100 K-9 howitzers - The Economic Times |url=https://m.economictimes.com/news/defence/ccs-clears-rs-20000-crore-make-in-india-projects-for-su-30-fighter-jets-100-k-9-howitzers/articleshow/116259513.cms |access-date=2024-12-12 |website=m.economictimes.com |date=12 December 2024 }}</ref> The contract, worth {{INRConvert|7628.70|c|year=2024}}, was signed with Larsen & Toubro on 20 December 2024 in the [[South Block]], [[New Delhi]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |date=2024-12-20 |title=Aatmanirbhar Bharat: MoD inks Rs 7,629 crore contract with L&T for K9 VAJRA-T Self-Propelled Tracked Artillery Guns for Indian Army |url=https://pib.gov.in/PressReleasePage.aspx?PRID=2086514 |access-date=2024-12-20 |work=[[Press Information Bureau]]}}</ref> The entire order is to be processed and delivered by the end of 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-13 |title=Indian Army accelerates artillery modernisation with indigenous systems |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/army-artillery-modernisation-indigenous-systems-pinaka-rockets-k9-vajra-advanced-artillery-guns-2664259-2025-01-13 |access-date=2025-01-14 |website=India Today |language=en}}</ref> On 3 April 2025, L&T signed another contract with Hanwha Aerospace at $253 million to execute the order. The indigenous content of the system is expected to be over 60% for the order.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clark |first=Colin |date=2025-04-03 |title=India to double Hanwha self-propelled howitzer buy, will manufacture locally |url=https://breakingdefense.com/2025/04/india-to-double-hanwha-self-propelled-howitzer-buy-will-manufacture-locally/ |access-date=2025-04-03 |website=Breaking Defense |language=en-US}}</ref>

